PRECONCEIVED.Definition: (of an idea or opinion) formed before having the evidence for its truth or usefulness

GIGANTIC.Definition: of very great size or extent; huge or enormous

SUCH.Definition: in more formal situations, we can use ‘such’ to mean ‘of this or that kind’

AS FUCK.Definition: (rude slang) - a phrase that usually follows an adjective as an intensifier

INTERPRET.Definition: to decide what the intended meaning of something is

UNAPPROACHABLE.Definition: someone who is unapproachable seems unfriendly or a little frightening so that other people are less likely to speak to them

GREW UP.Definition: the past tense of the phrasal verb grow up which means to gradually become an adult

PROJECTING.Definition: to wrongly imagine that someone else is feeling a particular emotion or desire when in fact it is you who feels this way

REINFORCE.Definition: if something reinforces an idea or opinion, it provides more proof or support for it and makes it seem true

MINDSET.Definition: a person's way of thinking and their opinions

DICTATES.Definition: to influence something or make it necessary

INTOXICATING.Definition: making you feel happy as if you are in a pleasant dream

CHARISMATIC.Definition: the quality of being able to influence other people and attract their attention and admiration

EXAGGERATING.Definition: to make something seem larger, more important, better, or worse than it really is

EXTRAORDINARY.Definition: very unusual and special; different in type or greater in degree than the usual or ordinary

OVER-THE-TOP.Definition: too extreme and not suitable, or demanding too much attention or effort, especially in an uncontrolled way

ATMOSPHERE.Definition: the character, feeling, or mood of a place or situation

ILLUSTRATE.Definition: to show the meaning or truth of something more clearly, especially by giving examples

NEITHER.Definition: not one and not the other of two things or people

ASSUMPTIONS.Definition: something that you accept as true, although you have no proof

CONTRADICT.Definition: (of one fact or statement) to be so different from another fact or statement that one of them must be wrong

OBSERVATIONS.Definition: a remark made about something you have noticed
